COVID-19 Status

As of 2:13PM PT yesterday, over 1.5 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 27.1 thousand have died.

In the last day, 4.2 thousand new infections were reported and 27 deaths. This is trending upwards.

Fortunately, 54.2 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 12 years and older, 84.8% have their 1st shot and 77.7% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is slowing down, but there are 9.6 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~113 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around Dec-12 when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children aged 11 or younger.
